-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Oct 3
-- 
-- Fri Oct 03, 2014 01:55AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, Oct 3 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Friday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- A human mistake, most probably at testing new production of explosive for the civil sector, could be the reason for the devastating blasts at an explosives factory in northwestern Bulgaria which killed 15 people, sources familiar with the investigation said. (24 Chasa, Monitor, Presa, Trud) CAPITAL DAILY - Debt collector Frontex company has bought out non-performing loans worth 94 million levs (60.81 million US dollar) from an undisclosed non-financial institution, the company said. -- Boiko Borisov, leader of centre-right GERB party, expected to win most votes at the Sunday early polls, appealed to Bulgarians to vote so that the country can have a stable government and avoid new round of elections. (24 Chasa, Monitor)